subject: resource/Jean_Doujat
object: Jean Doujat (1609, Toulouse – 27 October 1688, Paris) was a French lawyer, juris consultus, professor of canon law at the Collège royal, docteur-régent at the faculté de droit de Paris, preceptor of the Dauphin and historian. His works include histories of the reign of Louis XIV.He wrote an important Grammaire espagnole abrégée.
